title: Switch to unix line endings?
body:
[GitHub recommends](https://help.github.com/articles/dealing-with-line-endings/) to always use `\n` as a newline character in git-handled repos.

Windows line endings make it difficult to collaborate with folks using unix, and result in the docker-compose entrypoint scripts being parsed incorrectly on linux:
```
postgresml-admin-1     | /app/docker/entrypoint.sh: line 8: $'\r': command not found
postgresml-admin-1     | /app/docker/entrypoint.sh: line 23: syntax error: unexpected end of file
```

This should be an [easy fix](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1889559/git-diff-to-ignore-m/1889699#18896990). I haven't created a PR, because it would involve changing a large number of files...

title: Iris models always predict the same class
body:
Following the [iris classification example](https://github.com/postgresml/postgresml/blob/v0.7.0-pypi/pgml-extension/examples/classification.sql), you end up with a model that classifies every flower as `Iris-virginica`.

```
pgml_development=# SELECT pgml.predict('Iris Classifier', ARRAY[sepal_length, sepal_width, petal_length, petal_width]) AS prediction, count(target) FROM pgml.iris GROUP BY prediction;
 prediction | count
------------+-------
          2 |   150
(1 row)
```

This is the case for at least the following algorithms:

* linear
* ridge
* xgboost
* random_forest

title: [BUG] Unable to see snapshots generated from views
body: I created a view on some data, such as: `CREATE VIEW iris_view AS SELECT * FROM pgml.iris ORDER BY random() LIMIT 100;` and then trained a model with the following command: `SELECT * FROM pgml.train('Iris Classifier', 'classification', 'iris_view', 'target');` When trying to access the UI /snapshots, I got a `ProgrammingError`: ``` relation "iris_view" does not exist LINE 1: SELECT pg_size_pretty(pg_total_relation_size('iris_view')) ``` (but when I execute the size query in psql it doesn't throw an error; it just returns nothing.) I have attached a screenshot of the error.

title: A few fixes and adding DRF
body:
1. Fix migrations by ~adding `public` to search path~ explicitly using `pgml` schema for for Django tables.
2. Remove unused property `y_column_type` from `Snapshot`.
3. Added Django Rest Framework under `/api` in read-only mode. This helps if we want to fetch things dynamically via XHR, and also to understand what data we have in the database. It's available at https://localhost:8000/api.
4. Remove unnecessary `__init__.py` in `pgml-admin/` folder.
5. Rename `Contributing.md` to `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
6. Refactor `.sort()` to `sorted()`.

title: consider a client connection as an alternative to being an extension
body:
Being an python-linking extension introduces some interesting problems, such as python versions changing with OS upgrades.

Perhaps allowing for operation as a client -- but with a suggestion to run adjacent to the database instance, via container -- would improve adoption.
